BookOut Additional Remarks: The guest sent a complaint bur we got it after he checked out and waiting for the hotel's reply:good weekI am sending you this message from the hotel itself. while on vacation.Unfortunately at the reception at the hotel they initially claimed that the payment was not received and that you have to pay again. (Name of clerk Jana).Then after we explained that we had already paid and had an invoice so we asked them to do a double check they confirmed that the payment had indeed been received.Later when we wanted to go down to the pool it became clear to us that the pool is not included in the reservation and the payment for it applies separately. Then we noticed that other guests of the hotel could enter the pool.When we asked for explanations we were told that booking through you does not entitle you to enter the pool but only hotel accommodation. We asked to expand and they told us that only if you order on the website or via email the pool is included in the order. The way we booked the pool is not included. (name of clerk Natalia). She suggested contacting you about why you didn't specifically mention it in the order.We booked this hotel among other things because we wanted to enjoy a pool and not only the center of Prague after a rather long trip around the Czech Republic. We especially paid a slightly higher price for this hotel to get a hotel with a pool and unfortunately you misled us in the booking. We arrived for a weekend in Prague and of course it is not possible to change the order or contact you at the end of the week. In any case I expect you to check the matter with the hotel who is to blame for this. If the things they say are true you should have explicitly stated in the order that the price does not include entry to the pool.Beyond that the room we were given was on the first floor with an interior view into the neighboring room without an iota of privacy small and crowded we even thought it might be the servants' room.I don't know what your working relationship is with this hotel in Prague but it seems that they treated your order as if it were a foreign company unrelated to the hotel and as if they were doing us a favor by even honoring the order.I'm still abroad at least until the end of next week. I hope that the next hotel I stay in will have more fun.I would appreciate your referenceOshri Bartel  | Staff Name :
Resolution Additional Remarks: As per Marta from the hotel:Thank you for your email. I'm copying Travco through which the reservation was made. I would like to comment on the guest's complaint. Payment for the accommodation is provided by Travco however guests have beenasked to pay city taxes which are not included and are always payable on arrival. As for the complimentary pool it is indeed not included for guests through Travco but they can use it every day for a small fee. The price is approx. 45 EUR/hour and everyone is welcome in our pool including the public. The room that was assigned to the guests fully corresponds to the 3* standard to all the other rooms both in its equipment and size. Its location was with windows facing the courtyard where it is quiet and peaceful compared to the rooms facing the street where guests sometimes complain about the noise of trams and cars. Finally I would like to emphasize that we value every guest and treat everyone equally and professionally without any difference.The agent is well updated.
Rene from reception reconfirmed and guests are in house already
